OL,3,CKing's state visit shows need for
OL,4,CWhite House ballroom, says Donald Trump
OL,6,FHe added: "That's a big dig. We're
OL,7,Fbuilding a ballroom.
OL,9,F"Every president has said can we have
OL,10,Fa ballroom please, a room where you
OL,11,Fcould have a lot of people?
OL,13,F"So when the president of China,
OL,14,FFrance, when somebody comes over from
OL,15,Fthe UK, including the King, we have
OL,16,Fthe King coming over very shortly,
OL,17,FKing Charles, so we can have, like, a
OL,18,Flarge room, because the White House is
OL,19,Fincredible, but it never had a
OL,20,Fballroom.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774696008
OL,3,CKing's state visit shows need for
OL,4,CWhite House ballroom, says Donald Trump
OL,6,F"That'll be the finest ballroom
OL,7,Fanywhere in the world when it's
OL,8,Fcompleted.
OL,10,F"I love construction. I love building
OL,11,Fbeautiful things."
OL,13,FThe now-demolished East Wing was
OL,14,Foriginally built in 1902 during
OL,15,FTheodore Roosevelt's presidency and
OL,16,Fsubsequently expanded in 1942 under
OL,17,FFranklin Roosevelt.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
